'''亲从子名制'''（{{lang-en|Teknonymy}}），又称'''从儿称谓'''<ref>{{cite book |author1=中国社会科学院文献情报中心 |author2=重庆出版社 |title=社会科学新辞典 |date=1988-12 |publisher=重庆出版社 |location=重庆}}</ref>，指用一个人与其子女的关系来对其进行称呼的做法或现象，在全世界的多种不同文化中都有存在。“{{lang|en|Teknonymy}}”一词最早由英国[[人类学家|人类学家]][[爱德华·伯内特·泰勒|爱德华·伯内特·泰勒]]于1889年创造<ref name="Lee1973">{{cite journal |title=Teknonymy and Geononymy in Korean Kinship Terminology |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_ethnology_1973-01_12_1/page/31 |first=Kwang-Kyu |last=Lee |first2=Youngsook |last2=Kim Harvey |journal=Ethnology |volume=12 |issue=1 |year=1973 |pages=31–46 |jstor=3773095}}</ref>，是由表示儿童的[[希腊语|希腊语]]“{{lang|grc-gre|τέκνον|label=none}}”和表示名字的希腊语“{{lang|grc-gre|ὄνομα|label=none}}”组合而成<ref name="Reflections on Japanese Language and Culture 1987 p. 65">{{cite book |title=Reflections on Japanese Language and Culture |publisher=Institute of Cultural and Linguistic Studies, Keio University |series=Studies in the humanities and social relations |issue=v. 15 |year=1987 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bvALAQAAIAAJ |access-date=16 June 2019 |page=65 |quote=On the Notion of Teknonymy In the field of anthropology, the custom of calling the parent after the child is known as teknonymy, a term coined from the Greek word teknon "child" and the anglicized form of onoma as onymy "name".}}</ref>。

